<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="typification">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Typification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Thailand. Nakhon Ratchasima, Khao Yai National Park, Mo Sing To Nature Trail; 14°711'N, 101°421'E; on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1884" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Storenomorpha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Storenomorpha" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Storenomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp., attached to underside of unidentified dicot leaf; 10 February 2010; K. Tasanathai, P. Srikitikulchai, S. Mongkolsamrit, T. Chohmee, R. Ridkaew, A. Khonsanit (Holotype no. BBH 28509, ex-type culture no. BCC 41203, isolated from ascospores and BCC 41204, isolated from conidia). GenBank (BCC 41203): ITS = MT477071, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">TEF1</emphasis>
= MT503330, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">RPB1</emphasis>
= MT503323.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Refers to the capability of the fungus to produce pigmentosins.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Spider host completely covered by white to yellowish-white mycelial mat. 
<taxonomicName genus="Synnemata" lsidName="Synnemata" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Synnemata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
solitary or in pairs, cylindrical, white, becoming yellowish-white at the base (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4a</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Conidiophores</emphasis>
arising along the entire length of the outer hyphae of synnemata and from the mycelia covering the host, crowded, smooth to verrucose, (55-)97.5-170(-226) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(5-)7-10(-12.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, narrowing to a slender apex, and terminating in a swollen vesicle, metulae, phialides bearing conidia, forming a spherical conidial head (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4a, f</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Conidial heads</emphasis>
(25-)30-39(-45) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4g</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Vesicles</emphasis>
mostly globose, (4.5-)5.5-9(-10) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
diam (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4g</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="Metulae" lsidName="Metulae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Metulae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
borne on a vesicle, broadly obovoid, (5.5-)6-8(-10) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(3-)4-6(-7.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4g</figureCitation>
), bearing phialides. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Phialides</emphasis>
obovoid to clavate, with a distinct short neck, (5-)5.5-8(-9) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3(-4.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4g</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Conidia</emphasis>
produced on a phialide, obovoid with an acute apex, (2.5-)3.5-5(-5.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2(-3) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4h</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Perithecia</emphasis>
produced on the mycelial mat on the head and body of the spider, scattered, superficial with loose mycelia covering only the bottom one-fourth of the perithecium, ovoid, reddish-yellow, (790-)882-1,117(-1,150) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
300-443(-475) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4a, b</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Asci</emphasis>
cylindrical, 700-750 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, (4.5-)5-6(-7) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, ascus cap (4-)5.5-6.5(-7) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4(-5.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4c</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Ascospores</emphasis>
filiform, multiseptate, arranged in parallel rows, (666-)670-727(-730) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, often breaking into 128 part-spores (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4d</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Part-spores</emphasis>
bacilliform with apices rounded, (3.5-)4-7(-9) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5(-3) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Gibellula pigmentosinum a fungus on spider (BBH 28509); b perithecia; c an ascus with an apical apparatus; d ascospore; e part-spores; f conidiophores; g conidial heads; h conidia; i granulomanus-like asexual morph; j colonies obverse and reverse on PDA at 25 ° C after 28 days. Scale bars: 1 mm (b); 500 μm (d); 100 μm (f); 50 μm (g); 20 μm (c, i); 10 μm (e, h)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.72.55088.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/448318" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">4e</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="G.S.de Hoog &amp; R.A.Samson, 1978" authorityName="G.S.de Hoog &amp; R.A.Samson" authorityYear="1978" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Cordycipitaceae" genus="Granulomanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Granulomanus" order="Hypocreales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Granulomanus</taxonomicName>
-like asexual morph occasionally present, forming irregularly branched hyphae bearing mono- or polyblastic phialides. 
